Sentencas: Anode-supported microtubular solid oxide fuel cells (mT-SOFCs) using samaria-doped ceria (SDC) as electrolyte were fabricated, varying the composition and number of anode functional layers (AFLs), by combining the aqueous gel-casting and spray-coating techniques.
Titulo: Influence of Anode Functional Layers on Electrochemical Performance and Mechanical Strength in Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Fabricated by Gel-Casting

Sentencas: Suitable aqueous slurry formulation of NiO-SDC was prepared using agarose as a gelling agent for gel casting of tubular supports.
Titulo: Influence of Anode Functional Layers on Electrochemical Performance and Mechanical Strength in Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Fabricated by Gel-Casting

Sentencas: Afterward, 40:60 and 50:50 NiO:SDC (wt %) as AFLs and SDC electrolyte were deposited by spray-coating and subsequently co-sintered.
Titulo: Influence of Anode Functional Layers on Electrochemical Performance and Mechanical Strength in Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Fabricated by Gel-Casting

Sentencas: Finally, mT-SOFCs with 2.5 mm outer diameter and thicknesses of 380 pm support; 0, 12, and 24 mu m AFLs; 15 mu m electrolyte; and 30 mu m cathode were obtained.
Titulo: Influence of Anode Functional Layers on Electrochemical Performance and Mechanical Strength in Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Fabricated by Gel-Casting

Sentencas: The influence of AFLs on the performance and mechanical integrity was investigated for the three cells.
Titulo: Influence of Anode Functional Layers on Electrochemical Performance and Mechanical Strength in Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Fabricated by Gel-Casting

Sentencas: For this purpose, electrochemical and mechanical tests at both macroscopic and micro-/nanometric scales (at the AFLs region) were determined by flexural strength and nanoindentation techniques, respectively.
Titulo: Influence of Anode Functional Layers on Electrochemical Performance and Mechanical Strength in Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Fabricated by Gel-Casting

Sentencas: The results evidence that the use of AFLs with an adequate composition and microstructure in the mT-SOFCs is required to improve the performance and mechanical strength of the cell.
Titulo: Influence of Anode Functional Layers on Electrochemical Performance and Mechanical Strength in Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Fabricated by Gel-Casting

Sentencas: The cell with a single-layer AFL of 50:50 NiO:SDC (wt %) and 12 pm thickness exhibited the best performance (0.52 W.cm(-2)) at 650 degrees C using hydrogen as fuel and air as oxidant.
Titulo: Influence of Anode Functional Layers on Electrochemical Performance and Mechanical Strength in Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Fabricated by Gel-Casting
